                            <comment id="15386625" author="brstgt" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2016 21:02:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Additional Information:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We run a cluster on 3 machines with 3.0.8 and 3 machines with 3.0.6&lt;br/&gt;
I also found out that this error does not occur on all PKs, so may be this issue is either version related oder version-mix related.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15387595" author="brstgt" created="Thu, 21 Jul 2016 12:29:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Update:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After having updated all nodes to 3.0.8, the bug occurs also on rows that worked before. So I guess the bug was introduced in 3.0.8 / 3.0.7&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15392013" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 25 Jul 2016 14:41:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is due to an almost typo. Attached very trivial patch and unit test below.&lt;/p&gt;

